Katia Apalategui was inspired after seeing her mother cope with the loss of her husband by clinging to his pillowcase . 
  She came up with a way to capture a person's individual scent in a bid to help others in mourning . 
  French insurance saleswoman was inspired by her mother clinging to her husband's pillowcase seven years ago . 
  She teamed up with Havre university to develop a technique to reproduce the human smell . 
  The scent is extracted from clothes and made into a bottle of perfume . 
 